      "body": "The \"extra complexity\" is actually a fix to improved configuration. The current aggregated solution reusing `datacarriersize` has all signs of a hack. And is not surprising, as in the original goal was to deprecate.\n\nThe new feature allowing multiple OP_RETURN outputs warrants having its own very (simple and straightforward) configuration. And the usefulness is explicit: more control, not less.\n\nMiners can do whatever they want, from using Knots, to Libre Relay. But changing the defaults for the CORE software is not some trivial change.\n\n@pinheadmz why diminish the controversy you must be very aware of the v30 changes? Isn't is obvious the repo discussion will support the controversial change?",
